President Barack Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama will host members of the United States Olympic and Paralympic teams at the White House on April 21, 2010. The purpose of the event is to congratulate the athletes on their performance and thank them for representing the United States during the Vancouver Winter Games. The President and First Lady will also discuss the First Lady's Let's Move! campaign, which aims to solve the childhood obesity epidemic within a generation. More details about the event, including timing, location, and specific attendees, will be released at a later date.